review:
This is the best Total War game ever released in terms of:
- variety of armies and factions: every population has its pros and cons, everyone allows you to chose your own tactic, also there are a lot of them;
- AI competitiveness;
- Campaign;

More advanced than ROME II, and yet it allow you to do a lot more things than in Warhammer.

The AI is "special", the legendary difficulty only means everyone will attack you ignoring any strategic sense. They will abandon their settlements and try to attack you, even if that means they will lose that settlement. Battles are just moshpits and enemies will rush in bottlenecks to be massacred. Also the desync problem in cop multiplayer isn't fixed. Game will just randomly desync you.

Trying to play Co-op campaign and heres the result:

start game;
desync;
restart the, game try again;
desync;
restart the, game try again;
desync;
restart the, game try again;
desync;
exit game, uninstall.

What we've come to expect from CA and Sega. bad optimization, microtransactions, a derpy AI.

But I love it, theres no other series that makes a fight seem more alive. from the scale of the map to the clashing of the swords on the battlefield, this game is very immersive (until your soldiers climb up a wall and then take the stairs down :) )

if your not a Fan of a game with lots of disk based dlc thats sold to you bit by bit (at a reasonable price i'll add) or someone with a low spec PC the stay away from then TW series for the forseeable future. Everyone else have fun (I know I still am)

  I really enjoyed this game so far, it brought back some of the things that were missing in Rome 2, like a proper and playable game at realease (pun intended). The unites are fluid the graphics are over the top (that is if you have a powerfull enough machine, otherwise they are similar to Rome 2). Since Empire Total war that i did not have so much fun in a TW series like i'm having now. There's some polishing and patching to do still it's an awesome and solid release.

Pros:
        -Family tree;
        -Awesome Campaign, so excited to see the Huns burning the empires;
        -Reliable and (kind of) balanced unites;
        -New skill trees much more simple and easy to acess;
        -Nomad tribes brings a new feature to the game;

Cons:
         -Not much an improvment in the series, more like a polish on Rome 2;
         -Mac version needs urgent optimization (well what did i expected is a mac);
         -Politics hard to understand and mess around, much like Rome 2 politics are still a big part of the game and in my opinion should be more intuitive and easy to get around;
         -Incoming insane amounts of DLC that gonna rip my wallet apart;



Overall 8/10, possibily one of the best games of the year so far and certainly the best RTS for me.
